  "subject": "Change MaxRAMPercentage from 75% to 50%",
  "commit_message": "Change MaxRAMPercentage from 75% to 50%\n\n75% was too high given non-heap overhead (~350-450Mi). At 75%,\nthe container limit must be large to fit non-heap in the remaining\n25%. With 50%, heap and non-heap each get half the container,\nallowing smaller limits while maintaining sufficient heap for the\nobserved live data sizes (60-330Mi across SO pods).\n\nThe OOM Helm chart override (OOM-3391) sets JVM_ARGS via configmap,\nso this Dockerfile default serves as a safe fallback.\n\nIssue-ID: SO-4348\nChange-Id: I95ac3080a334ad2d82a040e64be0410201f6baf2\nSigned-off-by: Fiete Ostkamp <fiete.ostkamp@telekom.de>\n",
